<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chaldaea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I recently won a few nice items and my wisdom has jumped to 220.  I wanted to upgrade my armor a little and need suggestions.  First I lost the charred guardian shield and started using my Prismatic Shield so down to 211 wis.  I was thinking of losing my forest loops, mammoth cloak, one mith bracer, or gauntlets of the black.<P>Any suggestion on what I can use to replace these items?<P>Currently I am level 53 and my race is an Erudite.<P>------------------<BR>Chaldaea DeBebylon - Samsara</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalur - Veeshan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Keep the gauntlets of the black.  They are good AC as well as str and wis and such.<P>Keep the forest loops (unless you have something that is better AC).  For me, they each add 5 AC.<P>There is probably something that you can find for the back slot that will add more AC than mammoth cloak.<P>If you can get a Sebilite Scale Bracer (the one from Karnors) that will good to replace the mith bracer.  Higher AC, and +mana.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Dalur Stouthealer<BR>59th Dwarven Templar<BR>Veeshan Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">dusklar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sarnack shield is even better than the prismatic one from hate.. For a back slot I would recommend a Shield of Aegis if you don't mind the camping, or if you are one of those lucky random rolling clerics a heirophat cloak is good.  One other back slot item is the lozodial shield.. which I don't have yet, but seem to see more and more of those popping up.  One other thing you could consider instead of the earrings is your finger slots.. If you are using plat jaspar rings or even the velious ones, you may want to dump those for a golem ring or two.. or some other finger item rings that add ac. <BR>As far as gauntlets are concerned you could think about thunder etched gauntlets.. but they are pretty rare drop from what I have seen so far.  <BR>Dusklar 59th cleric </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">tailchaser</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Drop Forest Loops for Electrum Blue Diamond Earrings.  They're no AC, but they add something like +15 mana (which is better than Wisdom once you're above 200 anyway), and, if memory serves, 11vPoison, 11vDisease, 7vFire, 7vCold, and 4Vmagic, each.<P>If you can get your hands on a Donal's Bracer, swap that for the Mithril, and you'll make up the AC you lose on the earrings.  =><P>I'll echo the others on keeping the Gaunts of the Black; they're nice AC and +Str.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">There are alot of nice shields that are high AC and provide saves. Sarnak Battle Shield is probably the best, but unless you really need the saves, a Clay Guardian Shield is a nice alternative (AC25, +50hp)<P>I have an Aegis of Life, and even though it is 10wis, it is also 12AC and 25vs disease.<P>I would say that adding an Aegis would allow you to lose BOTH mithril bracers and put on a pair of Donals. I upgrade to Donals from an EM bracer and got 10 more AC.<P>To sum it all up, I would say, a Sarnak Battle or Clay Guardian shield, Aegis of Life (back), 2 Donal's Bracers, 2 Electrum Blue Diamond earrings.<P>This should add about 60-80AC, alot of resists. +30mana and drop you to 201wis if I did my math right.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chaldaea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I heard the Ageis of life is a nightmare camp.  Is it still really bad?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I wish I could answer that one. For me (12-14 months ago) it was a 20 minute spawn with a putrid skeleton as a place holder. All the other putrid skels spawned laying down, but in the middle of the camp was one that stood up. There could be 1 skel, Live Grimrot, Dead Grimrot, or any combination of 2 of the above. Saw once where 2 live ones spawned at same time.<P>I understand now its more like a 3 hour spawn with no place holders?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">greywolffe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">3 hours and 20 minutes to be more precise.  =D<P>Been looking in on old grimrot for quite sometime now.  He keeps missing our appointment and I'm begining to hold a grudge.  One of these days he's finally going to show up and I'm not going to be in any mood for his excuses so I'll just have to whack him.<P><P>------------------<BR>Greywolffe Silverstarr<BR>52nd Cleric of Tunare<BR>E'Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Walterscott</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You want to get the Electrum Black Sapphire Earrings actually.  They add AC equal to a Forest Loop, and have mana/hp.<P>What rings are you wearing?  If you are wearing the zero AC Wisdom rings, they would be the first thing to go.  I'd go for the Velium rings that are 6AC/65 HP.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Meddik</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Brodder had a suggestion on this a while back.<P>Just keep it at 220, but stay boozed up, so your effective Wis is still barely 200+.<P>------------------<BR>Meddik Sawbones<BR>Member of <A HREF="http://www.suvangi.com/drunkenbandits/" TARGET=_blank>Drunken Bandits</A><BR>(Bristlebane Server)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Islington</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Grimrot is the single worst camp this game has known.<P>I was playing my Paladin and got insanely lucky where the Dead version of Grimrot literally popped on top of me as I was running through the camp.  A few days later I spent 12 hours and 4 Place Holders trying to get a Live Grimrot.  I gave up when I found that a guildmate had the Scythe in his bank.  We chained the Quest and my Paladin now has an Aegis of Life.<P>I will NEVER get one for my Cleric though.  It's just too dang long.<P>With that being said though, the Aegis IS a GREAT item though.  If you want to do it, go ahead and camp the thing using the guides out there (kill the PH at the proper time to force a day/night spawn).  In between spawns, either log off or wander off or whatever.  I literally went AFK for 45 minutes and came back with no disturbances.  I set a timer for 3 hours to give me plenty of time to ensure that the camp was still mine.<P>It's a good item and if you go after it, good luck.  It's worth it in the end but I don't have the strength of will to do it a second time.<P>------------------<BR>Quistil Angelwatch<BR>Cleric of 30 Seasons in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<BR>Islington Angelwatch (Semi Retired)<BR>Paladin of 52 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr<BR>Phoenix Crusaders</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Chaldaea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What was this about not killing a standing putrid bone or something and protecting it?  I helped a cleric friend of mine camp and she would go nuts if anyone would kill any of the standing skels.<P>------------------<BR>Chaldaea DeBebylon - Samsara</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Georgia_TKR</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lose the mammoth cloak and get an aegis of life, then you can have even more wis to use to replace things with +mana items or AC items  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>I could possibly have around 230 wis right now and I don't even have my EM BP and I didn't use my bonus points when creating my cleric (I created her before the patch that first week to fix this issue).  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Getting wisdom at the 40+ game isn't hard at all... when I was in the lower levels I freaked out because I didn't realize I had to use those points til after it was too late  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Georgia Gaelicmyst<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Everlore Staff Member<BR>http://www.everlore.com/</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Islington</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok, here is how the Grimrot spawn works.  The Skeleton camp contains a bunch of Skeletons.  Inside the camp are a bunch of little “huts.”  One of these “huts” does not have a lantern on top of it, and it has 3 Putrid Skeletons sitting around it.  Inside the “hut” is Grimrot or his Place Holder.  The Place Holder is ALWAYS a Putrid Skeleton, will remain standing, and carries a rusty broadsword.<P>Now when you arrive at the camp and the PH is up, you’re lucky and can begin to camp it right away.  If not, you’ll need to wait for Grimrot or the PH to spawn.  This Skeleton and Grimrot are on a 3 Hour 20 Minute timer.  That means that you will get one pop every 3 hours and 20 minutes real time.<P>To get the Aegis of Life you need two items.  The Decaying Heart off of the Dead version of Lord Grimrot and the Pestilence Scythe off of the Live version of Lord Grimrot.  Note that the Dead Version will also drop a Scythe but it is not the correct one.  The correct one comes from the Live version and is a No Drop item.<P>To get Grimrot to spawn you must kill his Place Holder.  You should kill the Place Holder at 6pm Game Time to force a Live Grimrot to spawn (or another PH).  Kill the Place Holder at 6am Game Time to force a Dead Grimrot to spawn (or another PH).  What you are doing is ensuring that the next pop occurs during the day or night to get the proper version of Grimrot.  THAT is the reason your friend didn’t want anyone to kill the Standing Skeleton.  If you kill it at the wrong time, you will get the wrong version of Grimrot (or his PH).<P>That’s the reason this camp sucks so bad.  Grimrot is a rare spawn with place holders and an insane timer on him.  You can spend a 24 hour, real life day here and you will only see 7 or 8 Grimrot’s or Place Holders.  I got insanely lucky with the Dead Version.  He just happened to pop as I was going through the skeleton camp.  The Live version I camped for over 12 hours before chaining the quest with a friend.  The Aegis is great and I love mine, but I doubt I’ll do the quest for my Cleric since my Paladin grew so frustrated with the darn camp.<P>BTW, in between spawns I went AFK for large amounts of time.  I went shopping, I took a shower, I cleaned, I read a book, etc.  The camp is very safe and I never ran into anything that would attack me so long as I remained standing (as soon as I sat down, low green mobs would attack me).<P>Hope that this helps.  It’s a great item but it’s not fun.  Good luck.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Quistil Angelwatch<BR>Cleric of 30 Seasons in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<BR>Islington Angelwatch (Semi Retired)<BR>Paladin of 52 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr<BR>Phoenix Crusaders</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Puggins</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Heh, I got a couple of alterntae suggestions:<P>1.  Lose both forest loops.  Lug 2000pp worth of rubies to innothule and get yourself a Lynuga's hoop, which is 6ac 6wis 6hp.  Replace the other one with an electrum bs earring (ac2 hp35 mana25), sarnak earring (AC5 Str5), or cougar earring (AC4<P>2. I agree with replacing your mammoth cloak, but I don't think that the grimrot camp is worth it.  If you're gone camp something, I'd do the Hooded Black cape (AC10, hp45, STR5).  If you want to get original, buy a full plate cape from a human smith (AC12).  The enchanted version also has 2wis, which is a bonus.<P>3.  Jade rings have to go if you're still wearing them.  Replace them with Velium Fire opal rings (AC6 HP65).<P>4.  Easiest way to upgrade bracers: go to icewell and wait for a couple of the nodrop ac10 wis3 bracers to fall off guards.  Getting two of these drops your wis by 4 and ups your ac by 12.<P>If you decide not to camp anything at all, you can get a non-enchanted full plate cloak, 2 vel rings, BS earring and Lynuga's hoop for a few thousand plat and get the following adjustments:<P>AC +21 (raw)<BR>HP +165<BR>Mana +25<BR>WIS -18 (assuming you have vel jade rings, less if plat)<P>This will still keep you above 200 and increase your survivability by a ton.  Keep in mind this is the lazy method.  If you decide to do some non-masochistic camping as well, you can easily improve this quite a bit (enchanted cloak or HBC, cougar earring maybe, the bracers).<P>Just out of curiosity, can you list your equipment?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">KamuelaTZ</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The back piece is a priority for upgrade.<P>Otherwise if you haven't already, swap the jasper rings for fire opals or jade.<P>------------------<BR>Teir' Dal Vicar<BR>Tallon Zek</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JanSorensen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, 